   taining property after the occurrence of the drug transaction-including a bona fide purchase for value-would be eligible to offer an innocent owner defense on his behalf." 937 F.2d 98, 102 (CA3 1991).

   The conflict between the decision of the Court of Appeals and decisions of the Fourth and Tenth Circuits, see In re One 1985 Nissan, 889 F.2d 1317 (CA4 1989); Eggleston v. Colorado, 873 F.2d 242, 245-248 (CAlO 1989), led us to grant certiorari, 503 U. S. 905 (1992). We now affirm.


