   acter are not embraced within the issues that we granted certiorari to resolve, however, and for that reason, see Yee v. Escondido, 503 U. S. 519, 535-538 (1992), we express no opinion concerning the proper construction of that statutory term.

   The judgment of the Court of Appeals is affirmed.

   It is so ordered.
